               <p><persName><ref target="/persons/pers1106.xml"/>John Hutchinson Sr</persName>., a
                  merchant, and his wife <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1109.xml"/>Sarah
                     (&apos;Sally</persName>&apos;), were leading Methodists in
                     <placeName>Leeds</placeName>. Their son John became closely attached to
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2176.xml"/>CW</persName>. He accompanied
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2176.xml"/>CW</persName> on journeys in
                  the early <date>1750s</date> when his health, which was fragile, would allow. When
                  Hutchinson died in <date when="1754-07">July 1754</date>, <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2176.xml"/>CW</persName> composed three mourning hymns
                  (in MS Funeral Hymns).</p>
